sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant APIServer as API Server<br/>8000/TCP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP
    participant Processor as Batch Processor<br/>9090/TCP
    participant InfGW as Inference Gateway<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant GC as Garbage Collector

    Note over Client,InfGW: Flow 1: File Upload
    Client->>APIServer: POST /v1/files (multipart/form-data)<br/>Auth: X-MaaS-Username header<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)
    APIServer->>APIServer: Validate file (max 200MB, max 50K lines)
    APIServer->>S3: Upload file content<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: IAM/Static credentials
    S3-->>APIServer: Upload confirmed
    APIServer->>PG: Store file metadata<br/>TCP/5432, TLS (configurable)<br/>Auth: Connection string
    PG-->>APIServer: File record created
    APIServer-->>Client: 200 OK (file object JSON)

    Note over Client,InfGW: Flow 2: Batch Job Submission
    Client->>APIServer: POST /v1/batches<br/>Auth: X-MaaS-Username header<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)
    APIServer->>PG: Create batch record<br/>TCP/5432, TLS (configurable)
    PG-->>APIServer: Batch record stored
    APIServer->>Redis: ZADD to priority queue<br/>TCP/6379, TLS (configurable)
    Redis-->>APIServer: Enqueued
    APIServer-->>Client: 200 OK (batch object JSON)

    Note over Processor,InfGW: Flow 3: Batch Job Processing
    loop Poll interval (5s)
        Processor->>Redis: ZMPOP from priority queue<br/>TCP/6379
    end
    Redis-->>Processor: Job dequeued
    Processor->>PG: Fetch batch metadata<br/>TCP/5432
    PG-->>Processor: Batch details
    Processor->>S3: Download input file<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    S3-->>Processor: JSONL input data
    Processor->>Processor: Preprocess: FNV-32a hash sort<br/>for prefix cache optimization
    Processor->>Processor: Plan: SLO scoring & ordering

    loop Per inference request (up to 50K)
        Processor->>InfGW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer token / API key<br/>Headers: x-slo-ttft-ms, x-gateway-inference-objective
        InfGW-->>Processor: Inference response
        Processor->>Redis: SET progress update<br/>TCP/6379
    end

    Processor->>S3: Upload output file<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    S3-->>Processor: Output stored
    Processor->>PG: Update batch status → completed<br/>TCP/5432
    PG-->>Processor: Status updated

    Note over Client,APIServer: Flow 4: Status Check & Result Retrieval
    Client->>APIServer: GET /v1/batches/{batch_id}<br/>Auth: X-MaaS-Username
    APIServer->>PG: Query batch record
    APIServer->>Redis: GET progress counters
    APIServer-->>Client: Batch status with progress

    Client->>APIServer: GET /v1/files/{output_file_id}/content<br/>Auth: X-MaaS-Username
    APIServer->>S3: Download output file
    S3-->>APIServer: File content
    APIServer-->>Client: JSONL output data

    Note over Client,APIServer: Flow 5: Batch Cancellation
    Client->>APIServer: POST /v1/batches/{batch_id}/cancel<br/>Auth: X-MaaS-Username
    APIServer->>Redis: ZREM from priority queue
    APIServer->>Redis: RPUSH cancel event
    APIServer->>PG: Update status → cancelling
    APIServer-->>Client: 200 OK (batch status: cancelling)

    Note over GC,S3: Flow 6: Garbage Collection (periodic, interval: 1h)
    loop Every 1 hour
        GC->>PG: Query expired batches/files<br/>TCP/5432
        PG-->>GC: Expired records
        GC->>S3: Delete expired files<br/>HTTPS/443
        S3-->>GC: Files deleted
        GC->>PG: Delete expired metadata<br/>TCP/5432
        GC->>Redis: Delete expired keys<br/>TCP/6379
    end
